        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:29PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Harrisville, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harrisville, Pennsboro, West Union, North Bend State Park, Ellenboro,
Cairo, Pullman, Greenwood, Blandville, Avon, New Milton, Smithburg,
Mountain, and Berea.

This includes Route 50 in West Virginia between mile markers 36 and
59.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
